import numpy as np
import math

def boxcar_matched_filter(profile: np.ndarray, width: int) -> np.ndarray:
    n = len(profile)
    width = min(width, n)
    extended = np.concatenate([profile, profile[:width-1]])
    prefix = np.zeros(len(extended)+1)
    prefix[1:] = np.cumsum(extended)
    result = np.zeros(n)
    
    for i in range(n):
        result[i] = (prefix[i+width] - prefix[i]) / math.sqrt(width)
    
    return result
